{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b726fd65-199b-4219-b8fa-9ef4372435ee","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet run`, the test host stays alive and watches for code changes, re-running affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest pipeline and does **not** support the hot reload extension — it would just run tests once and exit.\n\nSo your workflow is:\n\n```bash\n# Set the env var (you said you already did this)\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1\n\n# Launch with dotnet run\ndotnet run\n```\n\nThe test process will stay running and re-execute tests as you edit your source files.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"516ef572-4260-43ed-9846-45962e330dfc","outputTokens":182,"requestId":"0833:27C56C:D65644:F93B39:69EAC9C4"},"id":"04efaf31-2d1e-4198-a498-1dbb9e014aee","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:39:22.556Z","parentId":"15a52397-b898-4a5d-a743-a7a4af0bd5ab"}
